==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rhamnaceous
<hw>Rham*na"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to a natural order of shrubs and trees
(<ord>Rhamnaceae</ord>, or <ord>Rhamneae</ord>) of which the buckthorn
(<gen>Rhamnus</gen>) is the type. It includes also the New Jersey tea,
the supple-jack, and one of the plants called lotus
(<gen>Zizyphus</gen>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhamnus</ent>⟦br⟧
